  "prompt": "How can I transfer from an international university to a US university as a US permanent resident?",
  "response": "To transfer from an international university to a US university as a US permanent resident, follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Obtain official transcripts from your current university\n- Ensure your credits are transferable\n- Check your GPA meets transfer requirements\n\n2. Research Universities\n- Look for schools that accept transfer students\n- Check transfer credit policies\n- Compare admission requirements\n- Consider schools that match your academic goals\n\n3. Application Process\n- Complete transfer application forms\n- Submit official transcripts\n- Provide course descriptions/syllabi\n- Write transfer essays\n- Get recommendation letters\n- Submit standardized test scores (if required)\n\n4. Additional Documentation\n- Provide proof of permanent residency\n- Submit financial documents\n- Complete FAFSA for potential financial aid\n- Verify English proficiency (if needed)\n\n5. Credit Transfer\n- Request credit evaluation from potential universities\n- Some credits might not transfer directly\n- Might need to take additional courses\n\n6. Visa/Immigration Considerations\n- Since you're a permanent resident, you'll have fewer complications\n- Maintain legal status\n- Update your address with USCIS\n\n7. Financial Planning\n- Compare tuition costs\n- Explore scholarship opportunities\n- Consider transfer scholarships\n\nConsult each university's specific transfer requirements for detailed guidance.",
